<BaseLayout title="About — The Lead Letter" description="About The Lead Letter, EntrLabs, and Joseph E. Iesue.">
  <article class="about-page">
    <p class="kicker">About</p>
    <h1>The Lead Letter</h1>
    <hr class="hairline" />
    <p>
      The Lead Letter is a weekly publication on leadership, service, and the discipline of helping
      people rise. It is written for people who lead — formally or not — and who take that responsibility
      seriously.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Lead Letter is published by
      <a href="https://entr.cc/entrlabs" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EntrLabs</a>,
      the research lab of <a href="https://entr.cc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ENTR</a>. EntrLabs
      develops frameworks and tools grounded in leadership research; The Lead Letter is where that work
      reaches a public audience, one idea at a time.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is written by <a href="https://josephiesue.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Joseph E. Iesue</a>,
      a leadership researcher and practitioner. His frameworks — Service Leadership, String Leadership,
      and ELEM — inform the thinking behind each letter.
    </p>
    <p class="tagline">Strength Through Service.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
